Third-party components are used under their own permissive licenses and remain
compatible with closed-source/commercial distribution, notably:
  - wana_kana (romaji<->kana)        : MIT
  - vibrato   (Viterbi tokenizer)    : Apache-2.0 / MIT
  - SudachiDict (dictionary data)    : Apache-2.0
  - rusqlite / SQLite                : MIT / Public Domain

Components with copyleft/share-alike terms are deliberately NOT bundled, e.g.:
  - GPL MeCab dictionaries
  - CC-BY-SA Zenzai model weights
The AI "magic conversion" headline feature uses cloud LLM APIs, so no model
weights are redistributed with this software.
